Many mysteries are hidden in that incident.

First, Korea has ambitions for the Sea of Japan.
South Korea once slaughtered Japanese fishermen and robbed Takeshima.
And South Korea tries to change the name of the Sea of Japan to a name that satisfies Korea's ambitions.
South Korea has repeatedly made groundless territorial-claims to Tsushima, Japan's peaceful island, and has repeated military exercises near Tsushima.

In such a situation, this incident occurred.
The scene of the incident was in the Japanese EEZ, where there were the South Korean warship and the unidentified North Korean fishing boat.
The South Korea has claimed that it was rescuing a North Korean fishing boat.
There, the South Korean warship encountered a aircraft of Japan on patrol, and fired radar.

Here are some mysteries.
(1) Why were the South Korean warship and North Korean fishing boats in Japan's EEZ?
(2) Why did the South Korean warship irradiate radar?
(3) Why did South Korean warship not respond to the aircraft's message asking the reason for radar irradiation?
(4) Why did South Korea not recognize the fact of radar irradiation immediately after the incident was discovered?
And, why did South Korea not apologize to Japan or take measures to prevent recurrence?

There is no clear answer from South Korea to these mysteries.
Please think about it.
